  "prompt": "What are the biggest differences between the Jeep Wrangler trims?",
  "response": "The Jeep Wrangler, known for its off-road capabilities and iconic design, comes in several trim levels, each catering to different needs and preferences. Here are the primary trims and their key differences:\n\n### 1. **Wrangler Sport**\n   - **Base Model:** The Sport is the most basic trim, offering essential features for off-roading and daily driving.\n   - **Key Features:** Includes basic amenities like a soft top, manual windows and locks, and a 5-inch touchscreen.\n   - **Off-Road Capability:** Comes with standard 4x4 capability and rugged suspension.\n\n### 2. **Wrangler Sport S**\n   - **Upgraded Features:** Adds more comfort and convenience features compared to the Sport.\n   - **Key Features:** Includes power windows, power locks, air conditioning, and a 7-inch touchscreen with Uconnect infotainment.\n   - **Off-Road Capability:** Similar to the Sport but with more comfort for daily driving.\n\n### 3. **Wrangler Willys**\n   - **Off-Road Focused:** Designed with off-road enthusiasts in mind, offering enhanced off-road features.\n   - **Key Features:** Includes bigger all-terrain tires, a limited-slip differential, and unique styling cues like the Willys hood decal.\n   - **Technology:** Retains the 7-inch touchscreen and includes additional off-road tech like hill-descent control.\n\n### 4. **Wrangler Sahara**\n   - **Luxury and Style:** Focuses on combining off-road capability with luxury and style.\n   - **Key Features:** Includes body-color fender flares, 18-inch wheels, and a more refined interior with premium materials.\n   - **Technology:** Adds features like an 8.4-inch touchscreen, Apple CarPlay, and Android Auto.\n\n### 5. **Wrangler Rubicon**\n   - **Extreme Off-Road:** Built for serious off-road adventures with advanced off-road features.\n   - **Key Features:** Includes front and rear locking differentials, heavy-duty axles, Rock-Trac 4x4 system, and disconnecting sway bars.\n   - **Technology:** Comes with advanced off-road navigation and the same 8.4-inch touchscreen as the Sahara.\n\n### 6. **Wrangler Rubicon 392**\n   - **High-Performance:** A high-performance variant of the Rubicon with a powerful V8 engine.\n   - **Key Features:** Includes a 6.4L HEMI V8 engine, enhanced suspension, and unique exterior and interior styling.\n   - **Off-Road Capability:** Retains the Rubicon\u2019s off-road features but with significantly more power and torque.\n\n### 7. **Wrangler High Altitude**\n   - **Luxury Focused:** Aimed at those who want a more luxurious Wrangler with high-end features.\n   - **Key Features:** Includes 20-inch wheels, leather upholstery, and advanced safety features like blind-spot monitoring.\n   - **Technology:** Equipped with the latest infotainment and connectivity options.\n\n### 8. **Wrangler 4xe (Plug-In Hybrid)**\n   - **Eco-Friendly:** Offers a plug-in hybrid option combining electric and gasoline power.\n   - **Key Features:** Includes an electric motor with a gasoline engine, offering improved fuel efficiency and lower emissions.\n   - **Technology:** Comes with advanced hybrid-specific tech and the same infotainment options as other trims.\n\n### Summary\n- **Sport and Sport S:** Basic to slightly upgraded models for everyday use with essential off-road capabilities.\n- **Willys and Rubicon:** More focused on off-roading with enhanced features for tougher terrains.\n- **Sahara and High Altitude:** Combine off-road capability with luxury and advanced technology.\n- **Rubicon 392:** Adds a high-performance V8 engine to the Rubicon\u2019s off-road features.\n- **4xe:** Offers a plug-in hybrid option for those looking for eco-friendly performance.\n\nEach trim level offers a unique blend of features, allowing buyers to choose the Wrangler that best fits their lifestyle and driving needs.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
